# Domain patterns (storefront / e-commerce)

## Auth and roles

- `User.id` is the Clerk user id string (e.g. `user_…`). Use `auth().userId` as the FK — no mapping table.
- Roles `USER` / `MANAGER` / `ADMIN` in Clerk `publicMetadata.role`, mirrored via `POST /api/webhooks/clerk`.
- In admin Server Actions and API handlers, also call `requireAdmin()` or `requireManagerOrAdmin()` from `lib/require-role.ts` after middleware.

## URL state (nuqs)

- Filters, pagination, sort, search: **URL state via nuqs**.
- One schema per feature in `hooks/use<Feature>Params.ts`; shared between `createSearchParamsCache` (server) and `useQueryStates` (client).

## Anonymous checkout

- Guest carts: `sessionToken` cookie → DB row (7-day expiry). `Cart.userId` / `Order.userId` nullable.
- Merge session cart into user cart on sign-in.
- Anonymous orders: flat `anon_*` columns (no FKs to user/address).

## Payments

- **CARD**: Stripe Payment Intents — create order `PENDING`, webhook `payment_intent.succeeded` sets paid → `PROCESSING`.
- **CASH**: order created immediately; admin marks paid on delivery.

## Human-readable order IDs

One-time DB setup: `CREATE SEQUENCE order_human_id_seq START 1;`

Generate in Server Action with `$queryRaw`, e.g. `'ORD-' || LPAD(nextval('order_human_id_seq')::text, 6, '0')`.

## Cloudinary

- Upload **from the browser** (Upload Widget); store `imageId` + `imageUrl` in DB.
- On delete product/category/brand: `cloudinary.uploader.destroy(imageId)` in the service layer.
